President Obama was briefed on federal preparations for the upcoming hurricane season and the coordination efforts between FEMA and state and local partners in hurricane-prone areas. The briefing included various officials from different departments and agencies. The administration's focus on disaster preparedness involves working with state and local partners, faith-based organizations, non-profits, and the private sector. During the briefing, participants discussed the steps taken this year based on lessons learned from past disasters. The President emphasized the importance of a comprehensive approach to disaster preparedness and the role of the public in emergency preparedness. The administration is committed to supporting state and local officials and will continue to take necessary steps throughout the season.